# --- COMSOL ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Lockfiles / recovery / autosave / logs from local solves
*.mph.lock
*.mph.recovery/
*.mph.recover
*.mph~
*.mph.bak
*.status
comsol*.log
comsolserver.log
*.out

# Model files are build artifacts — generated by Python build scripts, so
# the .mph itself is derivable from code. Ignore everywhere EXCEPT refs/,
# which holds the only .mph files we can't regenerate from code:
#   (a) supervisor-supplied reference models (Booth, SPEC §11), and
#   (b) frozen post-§5-gate "golden" models, saved WITHOUT solutions, as
#       a regression anchor against COMSOL version drift.
# Tracked .mph files are routed through Git LFS via .gitattributes.
*.mph
!refs/**/*.mph

# --- Project data: solves, surrogate dumps, MC output ----------------------
# Eigen-solutions and field handles are persisted per SPEC §1; they live in
# runs/ keyed by timestamp + COMSOL version + mesh hash, and are NOT
# committed (rerun from `sweep` instead). Add a runs/.gitkeep if you want
# the empty directory tracked.
runs/
data/
outputs/
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.npz
*.pkl
*.joblib
# EXCEPT refs/gate_runs/: archived licence-session gate runs whose numbers
# are cited from SPEC §8 / provenance/constants.py. Load-bearing provenance,
# not re-derivable without a licence session — tracked (npz via LFS), same
# rationale as the refs/ .mph exception above.
!refs/gate_runs/**
# AND refs/exports/: committed field-export reference bundles
# (docs/field_export_schema.md; schema examples / handoff artifacts).
# The npz is LFS-routed via .gitattributes; these are citation targets,
# re-derivable from refs/gate_runs records but frozen for the handoff.
!refs/exports/**
# AND calibration/data/: the Cowley-Semple raw archive (email + attachments,
# MANIFEST.sha256-pinned, read-only forever) and its derived artifacts.
# Load-bearing provenance, not re-derivable — same rationale as refs/
# above. The generic `data/` rule above silently excluded this until
# 2026-07-14 (commit 7f44606's "archive" message predates actual tracking).
# Both the directory AND its contents must be negated: git does not descend
# into an excluded directory, so `!calibration/data/**` alone is inert.
!calibration/data/
!calibration/data/**
# AND viz/data/: the committed presentation-layer bundle set (viz/PLAN.md
# R1 — bundles are committed so the viewer works from a bare clone over
# file://; git-lfs is FORBIDDEN for this directory for the same reason).
# Hash-pinned in tests/test_viz_bundles.py; regenerated via
# `python -m cavity.viz.export`. Directory AND contents both negated
# (same reason as calibration/data/ above).
!viz/data/
!viz/data/**

# --- Jupyter ---------------------------------------------------------------
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Plots / figures (selective) -------------------------------------------
# Track only what's in refs/figures/ or paper/; ignore scratch plots.
plots/
figures_scratch/
